    name: "Bandipur",
    category: "CULTURAL_VILLAGE",
    summary: "Bandipur is a beautifully preserved Newari hilltop market town at 1,030 m in Tanahun District, straddling the Mahabharat range between Kathmandu and Pokhara. Once an important trading post on the India\u2013Tibet route, the town was bypassed by the Prithvi Highway in the 1970s, accidentally freezing its architecture in time. Today its vehicle-free main bazaar of 19th-century Newari houses, Bindabasini temple, and sweeping Annapurna and Manaslu views make it one of Nepal's most charming heritage destinations.",
    story: `<p>Bandipur's golden era was the 19th and early 20th centuries, when Newari merchant families from the Kathmandu Valley settled here to trade along the strategic route connecting India's plains to Tibet's plateau. They built the robust, multi-storey brick townhouses with elaborately carved wooden windows and balconies that still line the main bazaar today. When the Prithvi Highway was routed through the valley below in 1972, trade shifted away, many families left, and Bandipur entered a long sleep. That neglect turned out to be Bandipur's greatest asset: the town's architectural heritage survived intact while other Himalayan trading towns modernized and lost their character.</p><p>Today Bandipur has reinvented itself as a model for responsible heritage tourism: the main bazaar is vehicle-free, several families have opened heritage guesthouses in restored Newari buildings, and a thriving community tourism program connects visitors with local artisans, farmers, and festivals. The Bindabasini Temple on the western bluff attracts Hindu pilgrims, while the cave system at Siddha Gupha (one of Nepal's largest caves) draws adventure seekers. In clear weather, the Annapurna and Manaslu massifs fill the northern horizon in one of the finest mountain panoramas accessible by road in Nepal.</p><h3>Highlights</h3><ul><li>Heritage bazaar street — vehicle-free 19th-century Newari architecture</li><li>Annapurna and Manaslu panorama from Tundikhel viewpoint</li><li>Bindabasini Temple and Khadga Devi Temple</li><li>Siddha Gupha cave — one of Nepal's largest limestone caverns</li><li>Thani Mai viewpoint for sunrise over Marsyangdi valley</li><li>Community-based heritage guesthouses and cultural programs</li></ul>`,
